				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$u\equiv j/\kappa \nabla T$$\end{document} is called the relative current density, which is the ratio of the electrical current density to the heat flux density by thermal conduction.Fig. 6
